</table>
<p class="ltx_p" id="S2.p3.5">The quantity <math alttext="\phi" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p3.2.m1.1"><semantics id="S2.p3.2.m1.1a"><mi id="S2.p3.2.m1.1.1" xref="S2.p3.2.m1.1.1.cmml">ϕ</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p3.2.m1.1b"><ci id="S2.p3.2.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p3.2.m1.1.1">italic-ϕ</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p3.2.m1.1c">\phi</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p3.2.m1.1d">italic_ϕ</annotation></semantics></math> can be considered as a generalization of the Newtonian potential in general relativity. The holographic screen is considered as a closed surface <math alttext="\mathcal{S}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p3.3.m2.1"><semantics id="S2.p3.3.m2.1a"><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic" id="S2.p3.3.m2.1.1" xref="S2.p3.3.m2.1.1.cmml">𝒮</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p3.3.m2.1b"><ci id="S2.p3.3.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p3.3.m2.1.1">𝒮</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p3.3.m2.1c">\mathcal{S}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p3.3.m2.1d">caligraphic_S</annotation></semantics></math> which is an equipotential surface with the same <math alttext="\phi" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p3.4.m3.1"><semantics id="S2.p3.4.m3.1a"><mi id="S2.p3.4.m3.1.1" xref="S2.p3.4.m3.1.1.cmml">ϕ</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p3.4.m3.1b"><ci id="S2.p3.4.m3.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p3.4.m3.1.1">italic-ϕ</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p3.4.m3.1c">\phi</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p3.4.m3.1d">italic_ϕ</annotation></semantics></math> at all its points. The Newtonian potential <math alttext="\phi" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p3.5.m4.1"><semantics id="S2.p3.5.m4.1a"><mi id="S2.p3.5.m4.1.1" xref="S2.p3.5.m4.1.1.cmml">ϕ</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p3.5.m4.1b"><ci id="S2.p3.5.m4.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p3.5.m4.1.1">italic-ϕ</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p3.5.m4.1c">\phi</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p3.5.m4.1d">italic_ϕ</annotation></semantics></math> is related to the Killing vector as follows <cite class="ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite"><a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#bib.bib92" title="">Wald:1984rg </a></cite></p>
<table class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_table" id="S2.E6">
