<p class="ltx_p" id="S2.p11.4">where <math alttext="C_{1}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p11.3.m1.1"><semantics id="S2.p11.3.m1.1a"><msub id="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1" xref="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.2" xref="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.2.cmml">C</mi><mn id="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.3" xref="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.3.cmml">1</mn></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p11.3.m1.1b"><apply id="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.2">𝐶</ci><cn id="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S2.p11.3.m1.1.1.3">1</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p11.3.m1.1c">C_{1}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p11.3.m1.1d">italic_C start_POSTSUBSCRIPT 1 end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math>-<math alttext="C_{6}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p11.4.m2.1"><semantics id="S2.p11.4.m2.1a"><msub id="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1" xref="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.2" xref="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.2.cmml">C</mi><mn id="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.3" xref="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.3.cmml">6</mn></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p11.4.m2.1b"><apply id="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.2">𝐶</ci><cn id="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S2.p11.4.m2.1.1.3">6</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p11.4.m2.1c">C_{6}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p11.4.m2.1d">italic_C start_POSTSUBSCRIPT 6 end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math> are constants.</p>
</div>
<div class="ltx_para" id="S2.p12">
<p class="ltx_p" id="S2.p12.1">Using the Killing vector obtained above in the component “<math alttext="tt" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p12.1.m1.1"><semantics id="S2.p12.1.m1.1a"><mrow id="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1" xref="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.2" xref="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.2.cmml">t</mi><mo id="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.1" xref="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mi id="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.3" xref="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.3.cmml">t</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p12.1.m1.1b"><apply id="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1"><times id="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.1"></times><ci id="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.2">𝑡</ci><ci id="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p12.1.m1.1.1.3">𝑡</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p12.1.m1.1c">tt</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p12.1.m1.1d">italic_t italic_t</annotation></semantics></math>” of the modified Einstein equation (<a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#S2.E12" title="In II Modified Entropy Gravity ‣ Cosmological Implications of Modified Entropic Gravity"><span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">12</span></a>), we find</p>
