<p class="ltx_p" id="S2.p14.4">In this relation, <math alttext="\rho_{b}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p14.2.m1.1"><semantics id="S2.p14.2.m1.1a"><msub id="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1" xref="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.2" xref="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.2.cmml">ρ</mi><mi id="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.3" xref="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.3.cmml">b</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p14.2.m1.1b"><apply id="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.2">𝜌</ci><ci id="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p14.2.m1.1.1.3">𝑏</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p14.2.m1.1c">\rho_{b}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p14.2.m1.1d">italic_ρ start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_b end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math>, <math alttext="\rho_{c}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p14.3.m2.1"><semantics id="S2.p14.3.m2.1a"><msub id="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1" xref="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.2" xref="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.2.cmml">ρ</mi><mi id="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.3" xref="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.3.cmml">c</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p14.3.m2.1b"><apply id="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.2">𝜌</ci><ci id="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p14.3.m2.1.1.3">𝑐</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p14.3.m2.1c">\rho_{c}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p14.3.m2.1d">italic_ρ start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math>, and <math alttext="\rho_{r}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p14.4.m3.1"><semantics id="S2.p14.4.m3.1a"><msub id="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1" xref="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.2" xref="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.2.cmml">ρ</mi><mi id="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.3" xref="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.3.cmml">r</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p14.4.m3.1b"><apply id="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.2">𝜌</ci><ci id="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p14.4.m3.1.1.3">𝑟</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p14.4.m3.1c">\rho_{r}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p14.4.m3.1d">italic_ρ start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_r end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math> are the energy densities of baryons, cold dark matter, and radiation, respectively. Note that this equation does not include the cosmological constant or any other dark energy contribution. Since the pressure of the baryon and dark matter components vanishes, therefore only the radiation pressure contribution remains in the total pressure relation,</p>
<table class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_table" id="S2.E38">
