<p class="ltx_p" id="S2.p17.2">where <math alttext="N_{\mathrm{eff}}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p17.1.m1.1"><semantics id="S2.p17.1.m1.1a"><msub id="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1" xref="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.2" xref="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.2.cmml">N</mi><mi id="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.3" xref="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.3.cmml">eff</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p17.1.m1.1b"><apply id="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.2">𝑁</ci><ci id="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p17.1.m1.1.1.3">eff</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p17.1.m1.1c">N_{\mathrm{eff}}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p17.1.m1.1d">italic_N start_POSTSUBSCRIPT roman_eff end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math> is the effective number of neutrinos, and we take it to be <math alttext="N_{\mathrm{eff}}=3.046" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p17.2.m2.1"><semantics id="S2.p17.2.m2.1a"><mrow id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.cmml"><msub id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.2" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.2.cmml">N</mi><mi id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.3" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.3.cmml">eff</mi></msub><mo id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.1" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.1.cmml">=</mo><mn id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.3" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.3.cmml">3.046</mn></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p17.2.m2.1b"><apply id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1"><eq id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.1"></eq><apply id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.2">𝑁</ci><ci id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.3.cmml" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.2.3">eff</ci></apply><cn id="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.3.cmml" type="float" xref="S2.p17.2.m2.1.1.3">3.046</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p17.2.m2.1c">N_{\mathrm{eff}}=3.046</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p17.2.m2.1d">italic_N start_POSTSUBSCRIPT roman_eff end_POSTSUBSCRIPT = 3.046</annotation></semantics></math> according to the Standard Model of particle physics <cite class="ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite"><a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#bib.bib95" title="">Mangano:2005cc </a></cite>.</p>
</div>
<div class="ltx_para" id="S2.p18">
<p class="ltx_p" id="S2.p18.7">In the following, we define the parameter <math alttext="\alpha" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.1.m1.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.1.m1.1a"><mi id="S2.p18.1.m1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.1.m1.1.1.cmml">α</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.1.m1.1b"><ci id="S2.p18.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.1.m1.1.1">𝛼</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.1.m1.1c">\alpha</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.1.m1.1d">italic_α</annotation></semantics></math> as the absolute magnitude of the acceleration, <math alttext="\alpha\equiv\left|\ddot{a}\right|" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.2.m2.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.2.m2.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.2" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.1" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.1.cmml">≡</mo><mrow id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.2" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.1.cmml"><mo id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.2.1" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.1.1.cmml">|</mo><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.2.cmml">a</mi><mo id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.1.cmml">¨</mo></mover><mo id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.2.2" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.1.1.cmml">|</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.2.m2.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2"><equivalent id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.1"></equivalent><ci id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.2">𝛼</ci><apply id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.2"><abs id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.2.3.2.1"></abs><apply id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1"><ci id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.1">¨</ci><ci id="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.2.m2.1.1.2">𝑎</ci></apply></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.2.m2.1c">\alpha\equiv\left|\ddot{a}\right|</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.2.m2.1d">italic_α ≡ | over¨ start_ARG italic_a end_ARG |</annotation></semantics></math>. Since this quantity has dimensions, it is more appropriate to normalize it as <math alttext="\tilde{\alpha}\equiv\left|\ddot{a}\right|/H_{0}^{2}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.3.m3.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.3.m3.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.2" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.1" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mo id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.1" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.1.cmml">≡</mo><mrow id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.cmml"><mrow id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.2" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.1.cmml"><mo id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.2.1" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.1.1.cmml">|</mo><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.2.cmml">a</mi><mo id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.1.cmml">¨</mo></mover><mo id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.2.2" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.1.1.cmml">|</mo></mrow><mo id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.1" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.1.cmml">/</mo><msubsup id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.2" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.2.cmml">H</mi><mn id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.3" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.3.cmml">0</mn><mn id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.3" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.3.cmml">2</mn></msubsup></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.3.m3.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2"><equivalent id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.1"></equivalent><apply id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2"><ci id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.2.2">𝛼</ci></apply><apply id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3"><divide id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.1"></divide><apply id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.2"><abs id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.2.2.1"></abs><apply id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1"><ci id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.1">¨</ci><ci id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.1.2">𝑎</ci></apply></apply><apply id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3">superscript</csymbol><apply id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.2">𝐻</ci><cn id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.2.3">0</cn></apply><cn id="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S2.p18.3.m3.1.2.3.3.3">2</cn></apply></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.3.m3.1c">\tilde{\alpha}\equiv\left|\ddot{a}\right|/H_{0}^{2}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.3.m3.1d">over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG ≡ | over¨ start_ARG italic_a end_ARG | / italic_H start_POSTSUBSCRIPT 0 end_POSTSUBSCRIPT start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT 2 end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math>. This parameter is dimensionless and so much easier to work with. In addition, we define the variable <math alttext="x\equiv\tilde{\alpha}/\tilde{\alpha}_{c}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.4.m4.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.4.m4.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.2.cmml">x</mi><mo id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.1.cmml">≡</mo><mrow id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.2" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.1" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mo id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.1" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.1.cmml">/</mo><msub id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.2" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.1" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mi id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.3" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.3.cmml">c</mi></msub></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.4.m4.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1"><equivalent id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.1"></equivalent><ci id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.2">𝑥</ci><apply id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3"><divide id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.1"></divide><apply id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2"><ci id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.2.2">𝛼</ci></apply><apply id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3">subscript</csymbol><apply id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2"><ci id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.2.2">𝛼</ci></apply><ci id="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.4.m4.1.1.3.3.3">𝑐</ci></apply></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.4.m4.1c">x\equiv\tilde{\alpha}/\tilde{\alpha}_{c}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.4.m4.1d">italic_x ≡ over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG / over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math>. In this relation, <math alttext="\tilde{\alpha}_{c}=\tilde{\alpha}(a_{c})" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.5.m5.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.5.m5.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.cmml"><msub id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.2" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.1" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mi id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.3" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.3.cmml">c</mi></msub><mo id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.2.cmml">=</mo><mrow id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.2" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.1" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mo id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.2.cmml">⁢</mo><mrow id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml"><mo id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.2" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml">(</mo><msub id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.2.cmml">a</mi><mi id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.3" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.3.cmml">c</mi></msub><mo id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.3" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.5.m5.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1"><eq id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.2"></eq><apply id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3">subscript</csymbol><apply id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2"><ci id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.2.2">𝛼</ci></apply><ci id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.3.3">𝑐</ci></apply><apply id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1"><times id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.2"></times><apply id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3"><ci id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.3.2">𝛼</ci></apply><apply id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.2">𝑎</ci><ci id="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.3">𝑐</ci></apply></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.5.m5.1c">\tilde{\alpha}_{c}=\tilde{\alpha}(a_{c})</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.5.m5.1d">over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT = over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG ( italic_a start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT )</annotation></semantics></math> is the normalized acceleration at the critical scale factor <math alttext="a_{c}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.6.m6.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.6.m6.1a"><msub id="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1" xref="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.2.cmml">a</mi><mi id="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.3" xref="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.3.cmml">c</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.6.m6.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.2">𝑎</ci><ci id="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.6.m6.1.1.3">𝑐</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.6.m6.1c">a_{c}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.6.m6.1d">italic_a start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math>. The critical normalized acceleration <math alttext="\tilde{\alpha}_{c}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.7.m7.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.7.m7.1a"><msub id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.2" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.1" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mi id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.3" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.3.cmml">c</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.7.m7.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1">subscript</csymbol><apply id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2"><ci id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.2.2">𝛼</ci></apply><ci id="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.7.m7.1.1.3">𝑐</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.7.m7.1c">\tilde{\alpha}_{c}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.7.m7.1d">over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math> determines the epoch at which the transition from standard Einstein gravity to modified entropic gravity occurs. With these definitions, we can now specify the temperature correction function which appears in the energy equipartition law (<a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#S2.E3" title="In II Modified Entropy Gravity ‣ Cosmological Implications of Modified Entropic Gravity"><span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">3</span></a>). We suppose this function is an exponential function in the form of</p>
