</tr></tbody>
</table>
<p class="ltx_p" id="S2.p18.14">where <math alttext="n" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.8.m1.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.8.m1.1a"><mi id="S2.p18.8.m1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.8.m1.1.1.cmml">n</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.8.m1.1b"><ci id="S2.p18.8.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.8.m1.1.1">𝑛</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.8.m1.1c">n</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.8.m1.1d">italic_n</annotation></semantics></math> is a positive constant parameter. In the limit of strong gravitational fields, the magnitude of the normalized acceleration is much larger than the critical normalized acceleration (<math alttext="\tilde{\alpha}\gg\tilde{\alpha}_{c}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.9.m2.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.9.m2.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.2" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.1" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mo id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.1.cmml">≫</mo><msub id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.2" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.1" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mi id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.3" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.3.cmml">c</mi></msub></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.9.m2.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1"><csymbol cd="latexml" id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.1">much-greater-than</csymbol><apply id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2"><ci id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.2.2">𝛼</ci></apply><apply id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3">subscript</csymbol><apply id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2"><ci id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.2.2">𝛼</ci></apply><ci id="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.9.m2.1.1.3.3">𝑐</ci></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.9.m2.1c">\tilde{\alpha}\gg\tilde{\alpha}_{c}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.9.m2.1d">over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG ≫ over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math>), and as a result we have <math alttext="x\to\infty" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.10.m3.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.10.m3.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1" xref="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.2.cmml">x</mi><mo id="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.1" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.1.cmml">→</mo><mi id="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.3" mathvariant="normal" xref="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.3.cmml">∞</mi></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.10.m3.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1"><ci id="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.1">→</ci><ci id="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.2">𝑥</ci><infinity id="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.10.m3.1.1.3"></infinity></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.10.m3.1c">x\to\infty</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.10.m3.1d">italic_x → ∞</annotation></semantics></math>. In this limit, we have <math alttext="f(x)\approx 1" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.11.m4.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.11.m4.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.cmml"><mrow id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.2" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.2.cmml">f</mi><mo id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.1" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mrow id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.3.2" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.cmml"><mo id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.3.2.1" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.cmml">(</mo><mi id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.1" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.1.cmml">x</mi><mo id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.3.2.2" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.cmml">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.1" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.1.cmml">≈</mo><mn id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.3" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.3.cmml">1</mn></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.11.m4.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2"><approx id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.1"></approx><apply id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2"><times id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.1"></times><ci id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.2.2">𝑓</ci><ci id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.1">𝑥</ci></apply><cn id="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S2.p18.11.m4.1.2.3">1</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.11.m4.1c">f(x)\approx 1</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.11.m4.1d">italic_f ( italic_x ) ≈ 1</annotation></semantics></math>, so, the effective theory of gravity reduces to Einstein’s standard gravity. On the other hand, in the limit of very weak gravitational fields, we have <math alttext="\tilde{\alpha}\ll\tilde{\alpha}_{c}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.12.m5.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.12.m5.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.2" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.1" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mo id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.1" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.1.cmml">≪</mo><msub id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.cmml"><mover accent="true" id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.2" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.2.cmml">α</mi><mo id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.1" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.1.cmml">~</mo></mover><mi id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.3" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.3.cmml">c</mi></msub></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.12.m5.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1"><csymbol cd="latexml" id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.1">much-less-than</csymbol><apply id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2"><ci id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.2.2">𝛼</ci></apply><apply id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3">subscript</csymbol><apply id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2"><ci id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.1">~</ci><ci id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.2.2">𝛼</ci></apply><ci id="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.3.cmml" xref="S2.p18.12.m5.1.1.3.3">𝑐</ci></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.12.m5.1c">\tilde{\alpha}\ll\tilde{\alpha}_{c}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.12.m5.1d">over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG ≪ over~ start_ARG italic_α end_ARG start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math>, and therefore <math alttext="x\to 0" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.13.m6.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.13.m6.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1" xref="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.2" xref="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.2.cmml">x</mi><mo id="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.1" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.1.cmml">→</mo><mn id="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.3" xref="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.3.cmml">0</mn></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.13.m6.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1"><ci id="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.1">→</ci><ci id="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.2">𝑥</ci><cn id="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S2.p18.13.m6.1.1.3">0</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.13.m6.1c">x\to 0</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.13.m6.1d">italic_x → 0</annotation></semantics></math>. In this limit, we have <math alttext="f(x)\to 0" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p18.14.m7.1"><semantics id="S2.p18.14.m7.1a"><mrow id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.cmml"><mrow id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.2" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.2.cmml">f</mi><mo id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.1" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mrow id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.3.2" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.cmml"><mo id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.3.2.1" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.cmml">(</mo><mi id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.1" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.1.cmml">x</mi><mo id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.3.2.2" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.cmml">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.1" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.1.cmml">→</mo><mn id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.3" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.3.cmml">0</mn></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p18.14.m7.1b"><apply id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2"><ci id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.1">→</ci><apply id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2"><times id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.1"></times><ci id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.2.2">𝑓</ci><ci id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.1">𝑥</ci></apply><cn id="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S2.p18.14.m7.1.2.3">0</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p18.14.m7.1c">f(x)\to 0</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p18.14.m7.1d">italic_f ( italic_x ) → 0</annotation></semantics></math>. Thus, in the limit of very weak gravitational fields, the theory of modified entropic gravity dominates, and hence significant deviations from Einstein’s general relativity are expected.</p>
</div>
<div class="ltx_para" id="S2.p19">
<p class="ltx_p" id="S2.p19.1">By substituting the function <math alttext="f(x)" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S2.p19.1.m1.1"><semantics id="S2.p19.1.m1.1a"><mrow id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.cmml"><mi id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.2" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.2.cmml">f</mi><mo id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.1" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mrow id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.3.2" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.cmml"><mo id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.3.2.1" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.cmml">(</mo><mi id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.1" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.1.cmml">x</mi><mo id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.3.2.2" stretchy="false" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.cmml">)</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S2.p19.1.m1.1b"><apply id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.cmml" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2"><times id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.1"></times><ci id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.2.2">𝑓</ci><ci id="S2.p19.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S2.p19.1.m1.1.1">𝑥</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S2.p19.1.m1.1c">f(x)</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S2.p19.1.m1.1d">italic_f ( italic_x )</annotation></semantics></math> from equation (<a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#S2.E48" title="In II Modified Entropy Gravity ‣ Cosmological Implications of Modified Entropic Gravity"><span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">48</span></a>) into the second Friedmann equation (<a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#S2.E34" title="In II Modified Entropy Gravity ‣ Cosmological Implications of Modified Entropic Gravity"><span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">34</span></a>), we arrive at the following equation</p>
<table class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_table" id="S2.E49">
<tbody><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_align_center"><math alttext="\tilde{\alpha}\exp\left[\left(\frac{\tilde{\alpha}}{\tilde{\alpha}_{c}}\right)%
^{n}\right]=\frac{1}{2a^{3}}\left[\left(\text{$\Omega$}_{b0}+\text{$\Omega$}_{%
