</div>
<div class="ltx_para" id="S3.SS3.p3">
<p class="ltx_p" id="S3.SS3.p3.1">In addition, <math alttext="l_{a}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1"><semantics id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1a"><msub id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1" xref="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.2" xref="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.2.cmml">l</mi><mi id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.3" xref="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.3.cmml">a</mi></msub><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1b"><apply id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.2">𝑙</ci><ci id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1.1.3">𝑎</ci></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1c">l_{a}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S3.SS3.p3.1.m1.1d">italic_l start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_a end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math> is the angular distance of the sound horizon at the time of decoupling, and it is specified by the following equation</p>
<table class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_table" id="S3.E63">
<tbody><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
