<div class="ltx_para" id="S4.p2">
<p class="ltx_p" id="S4.p2.5">To examine the consistency of the standard cosmological model (<math alttext="\Lambda" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p2.1.m1.1"><semantics id="S4.p2.1.m1.1a"><mi id="S4.p2.1.m1.1.1" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p2.1.m1.1.1.cmml">Λ</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p2.1.m1.1b"><ci id="S4.p2.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.1.m1.1.1">Λ</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p2.1.m1.1c">\Lambda</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p2.1.m1.1d">roman_Λ</annotation></semantics></math>CDM) with the given datasets, the free parameters are <math alttext="\{h,\Omega_{b},\Omega_{c}\}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p2.2.m2.3"><semantics id="S4.p2.2.m2.3a"><mrow id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.3.cmml"><mo id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.3" stretchy="false" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.3.cmml">{</mo><mi id="S4.p2.2.m2.1.1" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.1.1.cmml">h</mi><mo id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.4" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.3.cmml">,</mo><msub id="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.2.cmml">Ω</mi><mi id="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.3" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.3.cmml">b</mi></msub><mo id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.5" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.3.cmml">,</mo><msub id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.cmml"><mi id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.2.cmml">Ω</mi><mi id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.3" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.3.cmml">c</mi></msub><mo id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.6" stretchy="false" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.3.cmml">}</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p2.2.m2.3b"><set id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.3.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2"><ci id="S4.p2.2.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.1.1">ℎ</ci><apply id="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.2">Ω</ci><ci id="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.2.2.1.1.3">𝑏</ci></apply><apply id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.2.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.2">Ω</ci><ci id="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.3.cmml" xref="S4.p2.2.m2.3.3.2.2.3">𝑐</ci></apply></set></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p2.2.m2.3c">\{h,\Omega_{b},\Omega_{c}\}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p2.2.m2.3d">{ italic_h , roman_Ω start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_b end_POSTSUBSCRIPT , roman_Ω start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT }</annotation></semantics></math>. In our modified entropic gravity model, the free parameters are <math alttext="\{h,\Omega_{b},\Omega_{c}\}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p2.3.m3.3"><semantics id="S4.p2.3.m3.3a"><mrow id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.3.cmml"><mo id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.3" stretchy="false" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.3.cmml">{</mo><mi id="S4.p2.3.m3.1.1" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.1.1.cmml">h</mi><mo id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.4" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.3.cmml">,</mo><msub id="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.2.cmml">Ω</mi><mi id="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.3" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.3.cmml">b</mi></msub><mo id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.5" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.3.cmml">,</mo><msub id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.cmml"><mi id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.2.cmml">Ω</mi><mi id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.3" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.3.cmml">c</mi></msub><mo id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.6" stretchy="false" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.3.cmml">}</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p2.3.m3.3b"><set id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.3.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2"><ci id="S4.p2.3.m3.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.1.1">ℎ</ci><apply id="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.2">Ω</ci><ci id="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.2.2.1.1.3">𝑏</ci></apply><apply id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.2.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.2">Ω</ci><ci id="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.3.cmml" xref="S4.p2.3.m3.3.3.2.2.3">𝑐</ci></apply></set></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p2.3.m3.3c">\{h,\Omega_{b},\Omega_{c}\}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p2.3.m3.3d">{ italic_h , roman_Ω start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_b end_POSTSUBSCRIPT , roman_Ω start_POSTSUBSCRIPT italic_c end_POSTSUBSCRIPT }</annotation></semantics></math>. Thus, our cosmological model has only one more degree of freedom than the <math alttext="\Lambda" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p2.4.m4.1"><semantics id="S4.p2.4.m4.1a"><mi id="S4.p2.4.m4.1.1" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p2.4.m4.1.1.cmml">Λ</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p2.4.m4.1b"><ci id="S4.p2.4.m4.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.4.m4.1.1">Λ</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p2.4.m4.1c">\Lambda</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p2.4.m4.1d">roman_Λ</annotation></semantics></math>CDM model. The assumed priors for the free parameters of the <math alttext="\Lambda" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p2.5.m5.1"><semantics id="S4.p2.5.m5.1a"><mi id="S4.p2.5.m5.1.1" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p2.5.m5.1.1.cmml">Λ</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p2.5.m5.1b"><ci id="S4.p2.5.m5.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p2.5.m5.1.1">Λ</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p2.5.m5.1c">\Lambda</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p2.5.m5.1d">roman_Λ</annotation></semantics></math>CDM model and our cosmological model are reported in Table <a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#S4.T2" title="Table 2 ‣ IV Results ‣ Cosmological Implications of Modified Entropic Gravity"><span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">2</span></a>. The probability distributions for the starting values of each chain in all these priors are assumed to be uniform. With these priors, we performed our MCMC analysis and generated the Markov chains. For statistical analysis of the Markov chains, we used the publicly available GetDist package <cite class="ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite"><a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#bib.bib108" title="">Lewis:2019xzd </a></cite>.</p>
</div>
<figure class="ltx_table" id="S4.T2">
<figcaption class="ltx_caption ltx_centering"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_table">Table 2: </span>The priors for the free parameters used in our MCMC analysis. The priors of all the parameters are considered with a uniform probability distribution.</figcaption>
