<div class="ltx_para" id="S4.p4">
<p class="ltx_p" id="S4.p4.5">In Table <a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#S4.T4" title="Table 4 ‣ IV Results ‣ Cosmological Implications of Modified Entropic Gravity"><span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">4</span></a>, MCMC results for the <math alttext="\chi^{2}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p4.1.m1.1"><semantics id="S4.p4.1.m1.1a"><msup id="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1" xref="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.2" xref="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.2.cmml">χ</mi><mn id="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.3" xref="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.3.cmml">2</mn></msup><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p4.1.m1.1b"><apply id="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1">superscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.2">𝜒</ci><cn id="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.p4.1.m1.1.1.3">2</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p4.1.m1.1c">\chi^{2}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p4.1.m1.1d">italic_χ start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT 2 end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math> values for different datasets in the models studied are presented. This table shows that MEC fits with the CMB and SH0ES data better than <math alttext="\Lambda" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p4.2.m2.1"><semantics id="S4.p4.2.m2.1a"><mi id="S4.p4.2.m2.1.1" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p4.2.m2.1.1.cmml">Λ</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p4.2.m2.1b"><ci id="S4.p4.2.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p4.2.m2.1.1">Λ</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p4.2.m2.1c">\Lambda</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p4.2.m2.1d">roman_Λ</annotation></semantics></math>CDM. In turn, <math alttext="\Lambda" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p4.3.m3.1"><semantics id="S4.p4.3.m3.1a"><mi id="S4.p4.3.m3.1.1" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p4.3.m3.1.1.cmml">Λ</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p4.3.m3.1b"><ci id="S4.p4.3.m3.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p4.3.m3.1.1">Λ</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p4.3.m3.1c">\Lambda</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p4.3.m3.1d">roman_Λ</annotation></semantics></math>CDM provides a better fit to the SN and BAO data. The value of <math alttext="\chi_{\mathrm{total}}^{2}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p4.4.m4.1"><semantics id="S4.p4.4.m4.1a"><msubsup id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.2" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.2.cmml">χ</mi><mi id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.3" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.3.cmml">total</mi><mn id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.3" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.3.cmml">2</mn></msubsup><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p4.4.m4.1b"><apply id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1">superscript</csymbol><apply id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.2">𝜒</ci><ci id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.3.cmml" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.2.3">total</ci></apply><cn id="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.p4.4.m4.1.1.3">2</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p4.4.m4.1c">\chi_{\mathrm{total}}^{2}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p4.4.m4.1d">italic_χ start_POSTSUBSCRIPT roman_total end_POSTSUBSCRIPT start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT 2 end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math> in MEC is lower than the corresponding value in <math alttext="\Lambda" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p4.5.m5.1"><semantics id="S4.p4.5.m5.1a"><mi id="S4.p4.5.m5.1.1" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p4.5.m5.1.1.cmml">Λ</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p4.5.m5.1b"><ci id="S4.p4.5.m5.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p4.5.m5.1.1">Λ</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p4.5.m5.1c">\Lambda</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p4.5.m5.1d">roman_Λ</annotation></semantics></math>CDM, indicating that in general MEC fits the included data better.</p>
</div>
<div class="ltx_para" id="S4.p5">
<p class="ltx_p" id="S4.p5.7">In Table <a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#S4.T4" title="Table 4 ‣ IV Results ‣ Cosmological Implications of Modified Entropic Gravity"><span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">4</span></a>, we also report the values of the Akaike information criterion (AIC) <cite class="ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite"><a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#bib.bib109" title="">Akaike:1974vps </a></cite> for the models under study. This criterion is calculated using <cite class="ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite"><a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#bib.bib109" title="">Akaike:1974vps </a></cite></p>
<table class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_table" id="S4.E70">
<tbody><tr class="ltx_equation ltx_eqn_row ltx_align_baseline">
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_eqn_center_padleft"></td>
<td class="ltx_eqn_cell ltx_align_center"><math alttext="\mathrm{AIC}=\chi_{{\rm tot}}^{2}+2k\,," class="ltx_Math" display="block" id="S4.E70.m1.1"><semantics id="S4.E70.m1.1a"><mrow id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.cmml"><mrow id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.2" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.2.cmml">AIC</mi><mo id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml">=</mo><mrow id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.cmml"><msubsup id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.cmml"><mi id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.2" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.2.cmml">χ</mi><mi id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.3" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.3.cmml">tot</mi><mn id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.3" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.3.cmml">2</mn></msubsup><mo id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.1" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.1.cmml">+</mo><mrow id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.cmml"><mn id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.2" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.2.cmml">2</mn><mo id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.1" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mi id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.3" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.3.cmml">k</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.2" lspace="0.170em" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.cmml">,</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.E70.m1.1b"><apply id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1"><eq id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.1"></eq><ci id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.2">AIC</ci><apply id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3"><plus id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.1.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.1"></plus><apply id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2">superscript</csymbol><apply id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.2.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.2">𝜒</ci><ci id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.3.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.2.3">tot</ci></apply><cn id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.2.3">2</cn></apply><apply id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3"><times id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.1.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.1"></times><cn id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.2.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.2">2</cn><ci id="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.3.cmml" xref="S4.E70.m1.1.1.1.1.3.3.3">𝑘</ci></apply></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.E70.m1.1c">\mathrm{AIC}=\chi_{{\rm tot}}^{2}+2k\,,</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.E70.m1.1d">roman_AIC = italic_χ start_POSTSUBSCRIPT roman_tot end_POSTSUBSCRIPT start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT 2 end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT + 2 italic_k ,</annotation></semantics></math></td>
