<p class="ltx_p" id="S4.p5.6">where <math alttext="k" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p5.1.m1.1"><semantics id="S4.p5.1.m1.1a"><mi id="S4.p5.1.m1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.1.m1.1.1.cmml">k</mi><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p5.1.m1.1b"><ci id="S4.p5.1.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.1.m1.1.1">𝑘</ci></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p5.1.m1.1c">k</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p5.1.m1.1d">italic_k</annotation></semantics></math> represents the number of free parameters of the model under study. To evaluate the acceptability of these models, it is appropriate to assess the value of <math alttext="\Delta\mathrm{AIC}=\mathrm{AIC}_{{\rm model}}-\mathrm{AIC}_{\Lambda\mathrm{CDM}}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p5.2.m2.1"><semantics id="S4.p5.2.m2.1a"><mrow id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.cmml"><mrow id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.cmml"><mi id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.2.cmml">Δ</mi><mo id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.1" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mi id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.3" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.3.cmml">AIC</mi></mrow><mo id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.1.cmml">=</mo><mrow id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.cmml"><msub id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.cmml"><mi id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.2" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.2.cmml">AIC</mi><mi id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.3" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.3.cmml">model</mi></msub><mo id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.1" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.1.cmml">−</mo><msub id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.cmml"><mi id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.2" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.2.cmml">AIC</mi><mrow id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.cmml"><mi id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.2.cmml">Λ</mi><mo id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.1" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mi id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.3" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.3.cmml">CDM</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p5.2.m2.1b"><apply id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1"><eq id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.1"></eq><apply id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2"><times id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.1"></times><ci id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.2">Δ</ci><ci id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.2.3">AIC</ci></apply><apply id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3"><minus id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.1"></minus><apply id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.2">AIC</ci><ci id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.2.3">model</ci></apply><apply id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3">subscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.2">AIC</ci><apply id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3"><times id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.1"></times><ci id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.2">Λ</ci><ci id="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.2.m2.1.1.3.3.3.3">CDM</ci></apply></apply></apply></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p5.2.m2.1c">\Delta\mathrm{AIC}=\mathrm{AIC}_{{\rm model}}-\mathrm{AIC}_{\Lambda\mathrm{CDM}}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p5.2.m2.1d">roman_Δ roman_AIC = roman_AIC start_POSTSUBSCRIPT roman_model end_POSTSUBSCRIPT - roman_AIC start_POSTSUBSCRIPT roman_Λ roman_CDM end_POSTSUBSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math>. According to the interpretations for this criteria in <cite class="ltx_cite ltx_citemacro_cite"><a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#bib.bib110" title="">BonillaRivera:2016use </a></cite>: (1) if <math alttext="\left|\Delta\mathrm{AIC}\right|\in(0,2]" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p5.3.m3.3"><semantics id="S4.p5.3.m3.3a"><mrow id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.cmml"><mrow id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.2.cmml"><mo id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.2" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.2.1.cmml">|</mo><mrow id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.2.cmml">Δ</mi><mo id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mi id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.3.cmml">AIC</mi></mrow><mo id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.2.1.cmml">|</mo></mrow><mo id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.2" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.2.cmml">∈</mo><mrow id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.2" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.1.cmml"><mo id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.2.1" stretchy="false" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.1.cmml">(</mo><mn id="S4.p5.3.m3.1.1" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.1.1.cmml">0</mn><mo id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.2.2" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.1.cmml">,</mo><mn id="S4.p5.3.m3.2.2" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.2.2.cmml">2</mn><mo id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.2.3" stretchy="false" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.1.cmml">]</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p5.3.m3.3b"><apply id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3"><in id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.2"></in><apply id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1"><abs id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.2"></abs><apply id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1"><times id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.1"></times><ci id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.2">Δ</ci><ci id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.1.1.1.3">AIC</ci></apply></apply><interval closure="open-closed" id="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.3.3.3.2"><cn id="S4.p5.3.m3.1.1.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.1.1">0</cn><cn id="S4.p5.3.m3.2.2.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.p5.3.m3.2.2">2</cn></interval></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p5.3.m3.3c">\left|\Delta\mathrm{AIC}\right|\in(0,2]</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p5.3.m3.3d">| roman_Δ roman_AIC | ∈ ( 0 , 2 ]</annotation></semantics></math>, the considered model is substantially supported by the observational data, (2) if <math alttext="\left|\Delta\mathrm{AIC}\right|\in[4,7]" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p5.4.m4.3"><semantics id="S4.p5.4.m4.3a"><mrow id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.cmml"><mrow id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.2.cmml"><mo id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.2" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.2.1.cmml">|</mo><mrow id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.2.cmml">Δ</mi><mo id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mi id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.3.cmml">AIC</mi></mrow><mo id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.2.1.cmml">|</mo></mrow><mo id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.2" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.2.cmml">∈</mo><mrow id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.2" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.1.cmml"><mo id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.2.1" stretchy="false" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.1.cmml">[</mo><mn id="S4.p5.4.m4.1.1" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.1.1.cmml">4</mn><mo id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.2.2" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.1.cmml">,</mo><mn id="S4.p5.4.m4.2.2" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.2.2.cmml">7</mn><mo id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.2.3" stretchy="false" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.1.cmml">]</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p5.4.m4.3b"><apply id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3"><in id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.2"></in><apply id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1"><abs id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.2"></abs><apply id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1"><times id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.1"></times><ci id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.2">Δ</ci><ci id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.1.1.1.3">AIC</ci></apply></apply><interval closure="closed" id="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.3.3.3.2"><cn id="S4.p5.4.m4.1.1.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.1.1">4</cn><cn id="S4.p5.4.m4.2.2.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.p5.4.m4.2.2">7</cn></interval></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p5.4.m4.3c">\left|\Delta\mathrm{AIC}\right|\in[4,7]</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p5.4.m4.3d">| roman_Δ roman_AIC | ∈ [ 4 , 7 ]</annotation></semantics></math>, the observational data considerably less support the model, (3) if <math alttext="\left|\Delta\mathrm{AIC}\right|&gt;10" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p5.5.m5.1"><semantics id="S4.p5.5.m5.1a"><mrow id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.cmml"><mrow id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.2.cmml"><mo id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.2" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.2.1.cmml">|</mo><mrow id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.2.cmml">Δ</mi><mo id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mi id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.3.cmml">AIC</mi></mrow><mo id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.2.1.cmml">|</mo></mrow><mo id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.2" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.2.cmml">&gt;</mo><mn id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.3.cmml">10</mn></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p5.5.m5.1b"><apply id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1"><gt id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.2"></gt><apply id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1"><abs id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.2"></abs><apply id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1"><times id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.1"></times><ci id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.2">Δ</ci><ci id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.1.1.1.3">AIC</ci></apply></apply><cn id="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.p5.5.m5.1.1.3">10</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p5.5.m5.1c">\left|\Delta\mathrm{AIC}\right|&gt;10</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p5.5.m5.1d">| roman_Δ roman_AIC | &gt; 10</annotation></semantics></math>, the model is essentially not appropriate and should be discarded. As we see in Table <a class="ltx_ref" href="https://arxiv.org/html/2503.08236v1#S4.T4" title="Table 4 ‣ IV Results ‣ Cosmological Implications of Modified Entropic Gravity"><span class="ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">4</span></a>, for the MEC model, <math alttext="\left|\Delta\mathrm{AIC}\right|=0.67" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.p5.6.m6.1"><semantics id="S4.p5.6.m6.1a"><mrow id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.cmml"><mrow id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.2.cmml"><mo id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.2" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.2.1.cmml">|</mo><mrow id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.2" mathvariant="normal" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.2.cmml">Δ</mi><mo id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.1" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml">⁢</mo><mi id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.3.cmml">AIC</mi></mrow><mo id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.2.1.cmml">|</mo></mrow><mo id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.2" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.2.cmml">=</mo><mn id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.3" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.3.cmml">0.67</mn></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.p5.6.m6.1b"><apply id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1"><eq id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.2"></eq><apply id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1"><abs id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.2.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.2"></abs><apply id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1"><times id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.1"></times><ci id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.2">Δ</ci><ci id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.3.cmml" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.1.1.1.3">AIC</ci></apply></apply><cn id="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.3.cmml" type="float" xref="S4.p5.6.m6.1.1.3">0.67</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.p5.6.m6.1c">\left|\Delta\mathrm{AIC}\right|=0.67</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.p5.6.m6.1d">| roman_Δ roman_AIC | = 0.67</annotation></semantics></math> and therefore the AIC analysis states that this model is considerably supported by the observational data.</p>
</div>
<figure class="ltx_table" id="S4.T4">
<figcaption class="ltx_caption ltx_centering"><span class="ltx_tag ltx_tag_table">Table 4: </span>The resulting values of <math alttext="\chi^{2}" class="ltx_Math" display="inline" id="S4.T4.2.m1.1"><semantics id="S4.T4.2.m1.1b"><msup id="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1" xref="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.cmml"><mi id="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.2" xref="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.2.cmml">χ</mi><mn id="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.3" xref="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.3.cmml">2</mn></msup><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content" id="S4.T4.2.m1.1c"><apply id="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1"><csymbol cd="ambiguous" id="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.1.cmml" xref="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1">superscript</csymbol><ci id="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.2.cmml" xref="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.2">𝜒</ci><cn id="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.3.cmml" type="integer" xref="S4.T4.2.m1.1.1.3">2</cn></apply></annotation-xml><annotation encoding="application/x-tex" id="S4.T4.2.m1.1d">\chi^{2}</annotation><annotation encoding="application/x-llamapun" id="S4.T4.2.m1.1e">italic_χ start_POSTSUPERSCRIPT 2 end_POSTSUPERSCRIPT</annotation></semantics></math> for each model and each data set. The table also presents the results of AIC for the studied models.</figcaption>
